<br>
I think you're all missing the point of my strategy. Basically you have 3 things hotkeyed in a hotbank. Your offhand weapon, a general inventory slot where you keep your shield, and the bash skill itself.<br>
<br>
Now, every time you see that bash button pop up, you quickly switch the shield into your offhand, hit bash, then put your weapon back into the offhand and repeat. Put the offhand/shield hotkeys next to eachother for maximum efficiency. Is that so hard? Sure, it might be a moot point after 55, but what about those other 54 levels?<br>
<br>
As for the raid aspect, if I'm not mistaken, you need exactly ONE warrior to gain and hold aggro. The rest of the warriors could be off doing whatever they want to, including training their other weapons skills. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nydia>Nydia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/18/02 3:56:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=825.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: &quot;it's not my job to bash&quot;</span><hr size=1> Just to clear some things up re the original example, at Faervas' (who is a notoriously bad typist) request: <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The bank of melees Faervas was in charge of healing were not the MT, or even his backup; therefore it was not their responsibility to hold agro.<br>
<br>
Second, the melees in the raid consisted of rangers (can't bash), no paladins or SKs (who could have) and warriors, and a monk.<br>
<br>
Third, no 'racial bash' warriors were present. <br>
<br>
Fourth, only ONE 55+ warrior was present (it was an old world mob - more specifically Phinny - we are referring to here), so stunning using kick was not an option.<br>
<br>
Fifth, the call to bash was given after the party had already TPWed once, so they knew what was coming, and had already been back to their POB once.<br>
<br>
Sixth, the pull on Phinny occurred after the party had already pulled multiple high MR mobs, which the spellcasters in the party had already reported as being unstunnable using spells.  <br>
<br>
Granted, this is a fairly unusual set of circumstances, but it underscores the point that it behooves one to at least consider the possibility that one might need to use unusual tactics from time to time, and at least keep a shield in the bank, and the skill at a reasonable level AND that sometimes one might be called on to change strategies on the fly (spellcasters switch out spells if the situation calls for it during fights all the time, guys).<br>
The success (or failure) of your raid might depend on it one day.<br>
