<br>
I played a half-elf warrior to 57...not the top, but high enough to say ghetto bashing is not difficult or an unreasonable request.  You are expected to keep a couple sets of gear to handle different situations.  Some of those sets of gear will do less damage or have less AC but they will be needed in some situations.  Not doing this because you consider it too much of an effort means you suck at your job.  No ifs, ands, or buts about it, you aren't a good warrior and you aren't a good player.<br>
<br>
Someone said great players take advantage of all thier skills &amp; that's it in a nutshell.  IMHO good warriors have all 4 melee skills, taunt, disarm, kick, beg, and bash as high as possible.  Neglecting any of those skills can reduce your effectiveness in some situations.<br>
<br>
EQ CAN be reduced to very simple button-mashing and zerg rushes but it isn't much fun that way...if you excel at playing your class and group with similar people you can do some cool stuff with one or two groups that takes the zergs 4 or more.<br>
<br>
